Useful links for using github with R and R Studio:

https://bren.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360015783772-Connecting-and-using-Git-Github-for-version-control-with-RStudio
This article outlines how to clone a repo using R Studio. 

https://docs.github.com/en/github/creating-cloning-and-archiving-repositories/cloning-a-repository-from-github/cloning-a-repository
This help-page outlines how to clone the repo in command line (recommended but more involved that above)


Note:
Feel free to add any other links
You can always make edits to the code on github itself, if that's easiest. Just download the repo each time, try out the changes and then
add it manually. This is the simplest way prehaps but definitely more involved.
